00053 bool Interleaved2of5::verifyContent ( const string *content )
00054 {
00055         string ASCIIstring = "0123456789";
00056         set< char > setOfASCII;
00057         set< char > ::iterator iter;
00058         for ( int nn = 0; nn < ASCIIstring.length( ); nn++ ) 
00059         {
00060                 setOfASCII.insert( ASCIIstring.at( nn ) );
00061         }
00062         for ( int nn = 0; nn < content->length( ); nn++ ) 
00063         {
00064                 iter = setOfASCII.find( content->at( nn ) );
00065                 if (iter == setOfASCII.end( ) ) 
00066                 {
00067                         cerr << "You are trying to encode " << content->at( nn ) << " which is not supported by this barcode type." << endl;
00068                         return false;
00069                 }
00070         }
00071         return true; 
00072 }

00150 void Interleaved2of5::encodeCheckCharacter ( const string *data )
00151 {
00152         int accum1 = 0, accum2 = 0;
00153         for ( int cc = data->length( ) - 1; cc > 0; cc-- ) 
00154         {
00155                 char eachOdd = data->at( cc );
00156                 accum1 = accum1 + atoi( &eachOdd ) ;
00157                 cc--;
00158         }
00159         for ( int cc = data->length( ) - 1; cc > 0; cc--)
00160         {
00161                 cc--;
00162                 char eachEven = data->at( cc );
00163                 accum2 = accum2 + atoi( &eachEven );
00164         }
00165         
00166         accum1 = ( accum1 * 3 ) + accum2;
00167         int checkchar = (char)kModulus -  ( accum1 % kModulus );
00168         
00169         string suffix;
00170         stringstream output;
00171         output << checkchar;
00172         suffix = output.str( );
00173         output.flush( );
00174         
00175         string *newString = new string ( *data );
00176         
00177         newString->append( suffix );
00178         
00179         if ( newString->length( ) % 2 == 1 ) 
00180         {
00181                 newString->insert( newString->begin( ), '0' );
00182         }
00183         completedDataString = *newString;
00184         cout << completedDataString << endl;
00185         encodeSymbol( newString );
00186 }
